    .columns.medium-10.large-11
      %h2 Learn

      %p Be sure that you prepare enough money to run your business for at least the first several months, as it may take time to set up before you have enough customers to be profitable.

      %p Starting a business can be expensive. Using the calculations and estimates from your business plan (link to business planning), decide if you have enough money to begin, or if you need additional money first.

      %p A business plan is required if applying for funding through a bank.

      %p Here are some ways to get additional money if you need it:
      %ul
        %li
          %strong City Loans:
          %span The City of Long Beach has a loan program for small businesses. City loans are based on the quality of your business plan as well as your resume and other personal qualifications. Credit score is part of the decision, but a low credit score might not prevent you from getting a loan. More information is available on the city's website:
          %a{ href: 'http://www.longbeach.gov/citymanager/economic-development/grow-long-beach-fund-loan-program/' } http://www.longbeach.gov/citymanager/economic-development/grow-long-beach-fund-loan-program/

        %li
          %strong Private Loans:
          %span Many banks will also give loans to small businesses. The requirements for these loans may be more demanding, however, and interest rates may also be higher. The Small Business Association (SBA) can help connect you with bank lenders:
          %a{ href: 'https://www.sba.gov/tools/linc' }


  .row.step-section.step-section-do
    .columns.medium-2.large-1
      .icon-container-square.background-lightblue
        .icon-do.float-right.show-for-medium
    .columns.medium-10.large-11
      %h2 Do
      %ul
        %li
          %input{ type:'checkbox' } Create a financial plan
          %ul
            %li Calculate how much money you'll need ("starting capital") to cover start-up expenses for your business.
            %li Financial Projections for at least the 1st year of operation. [Financial Projections template]
            %li Break even analysis: determine how long it will take for your business to become profitable. How many customers might you need? How long will it take to find those customers?
        %li
          %input{ type:'checkbox' }Work with the Small Business Development Center (SBDC) and the city's Economic Development Department (EDD)
          %a{ href:'http://www.longbeach.gov/citymanager/economic-development/' } to find city and bank loans that will help you get started.

